The White House is preparing for the 2018 Christmas season and is inviting local musicians, high school bands, choirs, and Christmas-themed entertainers to apply for the opportunity to perform during the Holiday Open Houses in December. Volunteers are also welcome to apply for decorating or other roles. The deadline for volunteer applications is September 3, 2018, while musicians can apply until September 17, 2018. All confirmed applicants will be assigned a specific date and time for their performance. Interested applicants can find more details and apply on the White House website. Any questions can be directed to Volunteers@who.eop.gov.